				<p>Can you clarify your question a bit?  Because the Roomba cliff sensors are mounted underneath the robot and only point down.  They get activated when that part of the robot physically hangs over the edge of a cliff.  The robot also has some infrared proximity sensors in the bumper (aka the light bumper) which can detect objects in front of the robot.  But these are not cliff sensors, and cannot detect "negative obstacles" like cliffs.  Perhaps you should narrow your question and be more specific with your terminology.</p>
